One True Thing is a 1998 American drama film directed by Carl Franklin .
It tells the story of a woman who is forced to put her life on hold in order to care for her mother who is dying of cancer .
It was adapted by Karen Croner from the novel by Anna Quindlen .
The novel and film are based on Anna Quindlen 's real life and her struggle of dealing with the death of her mother , Prudence Pantano Quindlen in 1972 , due to ovarian cancer .
The film stars Meryl Streep , Ren√©e Zellweger , William Hurt and Tom Everett Scott .
Bette Midler sings the lead song , `` My One True Friend '' , over the end credits .
The track was first released on Midler 's 1998 album Bathhouse Betty .
It was shot in Morristown , NJ , Maplewood , NJ , as well as in Princeton University .